            <h3>About: </h3>
            Hi! My name is Gira Chawda. Full time grade 10 at Glenforest Secondary School, 16-year-old entrepreneur and coder, founder of Cracking the Code which focuses on youth and teens to be able to code for free! I love to play guitar, play sports and adventure out into the world. I am ambitious with my goals and always strive hard to achieve them. I have been in many skill developing programs such as Doina Oncel's hEr VOLUTION, Sarah Wells' leadership launch, and GEM's mentorship program. I launched my e-book called "The Ultimate Guide to Self-Learning Python" on January 1st 2021!
        
            <h3>Mission Statement: </h3>
        I want to expand my coding platform using my coding knowledge to accomplish more technological opportunity for low-income families and in doing so also achieve happiness!
        
